<br>
First, in answer to your question, I am more than willing to continue to help the raid even if I win a Crown on the first night.<br>
<br>
On another note, my guild Companions of the Gate is doing isles 1 - 5 this Friday evening, Dec 13th, and I will be taking Kristi up with them. I have planned a continuation of the raid on Saturday, Dec 14th, beginning at 12pm (noon) Eastern time, but due to the holidays, I can't field enough people in the guild at this time. However, since Sslak and Kristi are on separate accounts, I can take Kristi to isle 6 on Friday evening, then use Sslak and Kristi to get people up to isle 6 on Saturday. I will pay for sky stones, coffins, peridots, etc. if we can get enough people to do it this weekend. I would like the first Crown defaulted to Kristi since I will be paying the costs (and Sslak uses the big coffins, so not cheap). OTOH, if people would rather pay their own sky stone/coffin/peridot/etc. costs, then there would be no default.<br>
<br>
If we can get enough people, then we can also do isle 7 again on Sunday. In any event, I will still attend the raid on Jan 17th to help out, although if Kristi has the Crown by then I can bring my level 62 (currently) Enchanter Jalil Dreamspinner with KEI for all the mages <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (if you need a KEI chanter)<br>
